HEADWORD: Nicolaitan
<hw>Ni`co*la"i*tan</hw> <pr>(n⟦icr⟧k`⟦osl⟧*l⟦amac⟧"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ait⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from <ets>Nicolas</ets> of Antioch,
mentioned in Acts vi. 5.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of
certain corrupt persons in the early church at Ephesus, who are censured
in Rev. ii. 6, 15.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

